Here are some of the Action points that are done in this PR:

- [x] Created a voice-command module
- [x] Integrated the voice trigger and google-speech kit library
- [x] Added the English model
- [x] Implented the wake word.
- [x] Integrated the recognition of the user's speech and translate it to plain text.
- [x] Both the integration has tested well.
- [x] Added all the Aimybox-specific code to separate a ``voicecommand`` module 

Trigger words:
1. listen
2. hey car

After testing the trigger word, here are some of the results: 
1. ``listen`` works fine.
2. while ``hey car`` works fine too but voice recognition also gets triggered by just saying ``hey``! 
3. While saying just ``car`` does not trigger!

Here are some of the notable work that are done in the GSoC'22 timeline:

- [x]  Created a voice-command module
- [x]  Integrated the voice trigger, google-speech kit library and added [CMU Pocketsphinx](https://github.com/cmusphinx/pocketsphinx-android) language model
- [x]  Implemented the wake word.
- [x]  Integrated the recognition of the user's speech and translate it to plain text.
- [x]  Both the integration has tested well.
- [x]  Added all the Aimybox-specific code to separate a voice command module
- [x]  Added voice command option in settings
- [x]  Ask for microphone permission after enabling voice command
- [x]  Added a check for microphone permission in the main activity
- [x]  Custom good-looking snack bar for voice trigger
- [x]  Modularized all the code inside voice command module to make it readable
- [x]  Integrated start recording voice command with the enviroCar application 
- [x]  Integrated stop recording voice command with the enviroCar application
- [x]  Integrated car selection voice command with the enviroCar application
